data.description: BASEMENT! POOL! This exquisite, executive home has 5,800 square feet including the basement, which makes this a fantastic deal. Every ceiling is at least 10 feet high, if not more. The vaulted foyer (with built-in display cabinets) is flanked with a formal living room and a dining/office, and faces the curving staircase to the 3 bedrooms and two baths upstairs. Upstairs, one of the bedrooms has it's own bathroom, walk-in closet, and walk-in attic. The other two bedrooms have their own walk in closets, with bathroom sink/granite countertops/cabinet, and share a toilet/bathtub/shower room. The kitchen has a huge eat-in area and island. Tons of cabinets. Newly renovated with granite countertops, subway tile backsplash, new appliances. A bonus room/office is open to the kitchen which leads to the large covered deck outside. The master bedroom has a sitting area with a bay window, large walk-in closet, large tile shower, his and hers vanities with granite countertops, and jetted garden tub. The laundry room is huge with a built-in ironing board and hanging racks. The basement has one room with a closet (but no window, but could be used as a 5th bedroom). The rest of the basement is one huge open space. IT has a sitting area by the fireplace with built in speakers in the ceiling. With space for a pool table, and air hockey table, and home theater, this place is made for parties!. The backdoor leads to a large patio. The pool (18ft. by 30 ft) is surrounded by a sidewalk, and diving board at the deep end. There is still plenty of yard and trees for utmost privacy. Property backs to a neighborhood pond. You must come see to believe!
